<li id="cite_note-CBO-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-CBO_7-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/69xx/doc6908/12-01-10PercentTaxCut.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/69xx/doc6908/12-01-10PercentTaxCut.pdf" rel="nofollow">"CBO. (December 1, 2005). <i>Analyzing the Economic and Budgetary Effects of a 10 Percent Cut in Income Tax Rates</i>."</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/69xx/doc6908/12-01-10PercentTaxCut.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/69xx/doc6908/12-01-10PercentTaxCut.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/69xx/doc6908/12-01-10PercentTaxCut.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-11</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=CBO.+%28December+1%2C+2005%29.+%27%27Analyzing+the+Economic+and+Budgetary+Effects+of+a+10+Percent+Cut+in+Income+Tax+Rates%27%27.&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fftpdocs%2F69xx%2Fdoc6908%2F12-01-10PercentTaxCut.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laffer_curve"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Moore.2C_S.-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Moore.2C_S._8-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMoore2003">Moore, Stephen (2003-03-18). <a href="http://www.cato.org/testimony/ct-sm03182003.html" class="external text" title="http://www.cato.org/testimony/ct-sm03182003.html" rel="nofollow">"President Bush's Economic Growth Tax Cut"</a>. CATO Institute<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.cato.org/testimony/ct-sm03182003.html" class="external free" title="http://www.cato.org/testimony/ct-sm03182003.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.cato.org/testimony/ct-sm03182003.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-11</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=President+Bush%27s+Economic+Growth+Tax+Cut&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Moore&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephen&amp;rft.au=Moore%2C+Stephen&amp;rft.date=2003-03-18&amp;rft.pub=CATO+Institute&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cato.org%2Ftestimony%2Fct-sm03182003.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laffer_curve"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.econlib.org/library/Enc/MarginalTaxRates.html" class="external text" title="http://www.econlib.org/library/Enc/MarginalTaxRates.html" rel="nofollow">Marginal Tax Rates</a>, by Alan Reynolds</li>
<li id="cite_note-Pecorino1995-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Pecorino1995_10-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFPecorino1995"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Paul_Pecorino&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Paul Pecorino (page does not exist)">Pecorino, Paul</a> (1995), "<a href="http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0304393295012249" class="external text" title="http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0304393295012249" rel="nofollow">Tax rates and tax revenues in a model of growth through human capital accumulation</a>", <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Monetary_Economics" title="Journal of Monetary Economics">Journal of Monetary Economics</a></i> <b>36</b> (3): 527–539</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%5Bhttp%3A%2F%2Flinkinghub.elsevier.com%2Fretrieve%2Fpii%2F0304393295012249+Tax+rates+and+tax+revenues+in+a+model+of+growth+through+human+capital+accumulation%5D&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BJournal+of+Monetary+Economics%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Pecorino&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul&amp;rft.au=Pecorino%2C+Paul&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.volume=36&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=527%E2%80%93539&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laffer_curve"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
